{"aid": "http://arxiv.org/abs/2504.15968v1", "title": "Global Compactness Result for a Brézis-Nirenberg-Type Problem
  Involving Mixed Local Nonlocal Operator", "summary": "This paper investigates the profile decomposition of Palais-Smale sequences
associated with a Br\'ezis-Nirenberg-type problem involving a combination of
local nonlocal operator, given by
  \begin{equation*}
  \begin{aligned}
  &-\Delta u + (-\Delta)^s u - \lambda u = |u|^{2^*-2}u \;\;\mbox{ in } \Omega,
  &\quad u=0\,\mbox{ in }\mathbb{R}^N\setminus \Omega.
  \end{aligned}
  \end{equation*} where $ N \geq 3$ and $2^* = \frac{2N}{N - 2} $ denotes the
critical Sobolev exponent. As an application of the derived global compactness
result, we further study the corresponding Coron-type problem.", "main_category": "math.AP", "categories": "math.AP,math.FA", "published": "2025-04-22T15:07:55Z"}
